shows.title: Interstellar
shows.overview: A team of explorers travel beyond this galaxy through a newly discovered wormhole to discover whether mankind has a future among the stars.

shows.title: Inception
shows.overview: In a world where the technology exists to enter the human mind through dream invasion, a highly skilled thief is given a final chance at redemption which involves executing his toughest job till date- Inception.

shows.title: The Matrix
shows.overview: Keanu Reeves stars in this futuristic sci-fi adventure that broke box office records. What is The Matrix? No one can conceive it, no one can be told what it is. It has to be seen, to be understood. This is the kind of future you don't dream about.

shows.title: Alien
shows.overview: Directed by Ridley Scott, the original sci-fi classic follows Ripley (Sigourney Weaver) investigating a suspected SOS on a remote planet and makes a terrifying discovery.

shows.title: Avengers: Infinity War
shows.overview: An unprecedented cinematic journey ten years in the making and spanning the entire Marvel Cinematic Universe, Marvel Studios’ Avengers: Infinity War brings to the screen the ultimate, deadliest showdown of all time. The Avengers and their Super Hero allies must be willing to sacrifice all in an attempt to defeat the powerful Thanos, before his blitz of devastation and ruin puts an end to the universe. Some flashing lights sequences or patterns may affect photosensitive viewers.

shows.title: The Prestige
shows.overview: Alfred and Rupert are two rival magicians in 19th century London. When Alfred performs the ultimate magic trick, Rupert tries desperately to find out the secret to the trick.

shows.title: Aliens
shows.overview: James Cameron's knockout sequel to 'Alien' finds Sigourney Weaver off to save a space colony on the planet where the first alien reigned.

shows.title: The Thing
shows.overview: John Carpenter delivers the ultimate in alien terror in this chilling story about an Antarctic research team that discovers a form-changing alien buried in the snow for over 100,000 years.

shows.title: Logan
shows.overview: In the near future, Logan's attempts to hide out on the Mexican border with an ailing Professor X are up-ended when a young mutant arrives, being pursued by dark forces.

shows.title: Jurassic Park
shows.overview: Steven Spielberg brings the unforgettable characters of Michael Crichton's best-seller to life. The guests of a theme park featuring genetically engineered dinosaurs must battle to survive when the dinosaurs break free.

shows.title: Nausicaä of the Valley of the Wind
shows.overview: Facing the destruction of her planet's natural resources, warrior princess Nausicaa rallies her people against an evil queen's rampaging army.

shows.title: Her
shows.overview: The future of romance goes digital in this unique love story about a heartbroken guy who finds love with his new operating system.

shows.title: Donnie Darko
shows.overview: Donnie is a bright and charming high school student who also happens to be frequented by Frank; a monstrous six-foot rabbit that only he can see.

shows.title: The Martian
shows.overview: From legendary director Ridley Scott (Alien, Prometheus) comes a gripping tale of human strength and the will to survive, starring Matt Damon as an astronaut stranded on Mars.

shows.title: The Terminator
shows.overview: A cyborg (part man, part machine) is sent from the 21st century to present-day Los Angeles to assassinate a seemingly innocent women whose child will play an important part in the world from which the killer came.

shows.title: Mad Max: Fury Road
shows.overview: Max (Tom Hardy) becomes swept up with a few survivors fleeing across the Wasteland in a war rig driven by commander Furiosa (Charlize Theron). They are escaping a Citadel tyrannised by a warlord, who swiftly pursues them in a high-octane road war.

shows.title: The Avengers
shows.overview: Marvel’s The Avengers is the Super Hero team up of a lifetime, featuring iconic Marvel Super Heroes Iron Man, The Incredible Hulk, Thor, Captain America, Hawkeye and Black Widow.

shows.title: Planet of the Apes
shows.overview: U.S. Spaceship lands on a desolate planet, stranding the spacemen in a world dominated by apes 2000 years into the future. Based on Pierre Boulle's novel.

shows.title: Edge of Tomorrow
shows.overview: An officer finds himself caught in a time loop in a war with an alien race. His skills increase as he faces the same brutal combat scenarios, and his union with a Special Forces warrior gets him closer and closer to defeating the enemy.

shows.title: Arrival
shows.overview: When a mysterious alien spaceship lands on Earth, an expert linguist is recruited by the military to decipher their language and figure out whether they come in peace or are a threat.
